  "market_context": "Price trades into a daily fair value gap around 30000–30400 after failure swings on Friday's low. The market is positioned at a discount POI where a weekly reversal is anticipated to develop through the upcoming days.",
  "key_observation": "Monday expands aggressively away from the FVG forming the weekly low; Tuesday consolidates; Wednesday manipulates the consolidation low with a candle 2 closure backed by an hourly change in state of delivery, signaling an intraweek reversal.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify price reacting inside a daily fair value gap (30000–30400) with Friday failure swings on the low as the point of interest.",
    "Observe Monday opening and expanding aggressively higher away from the FVG, signaling the area wants to form a reversal and set the weekly low.",
    "Note Tuesday produces a smaller-range candle 2 closure opposing Monday, suggesting a retracement to take out the previous day low (new FVG) before continuation.",
    "On Wednesday, see price manipulate the consolidation range low and form a candle 2 closure, signaling reversal back in the bullish direction.",
    "Drop to the 1-hour timeframe to confirm a change in state of delivery and identify a new continuation forming above the C2 zone (~31125–31305).",
    "Set expectation that the manipulation low must hold as price expands higher, with Thursday and Friday acting as continuation days.",
    "Observe Thursday delivers the large expansion higher; caution applied to Friday since a new phase of price (consolidation) may follow large ranges."
  ],
  "outcome": "Wednesday's reversal played out — Thursday delivered a large bullish expansion candle; Friday continued but less cleanly, coming back into the range.",
  "lessons": "An intraweek reversal can form when Monday sets the low, Tuesday consolidates, and Wednesday manipulates the low with a candle 2 closure plus hourly CISD. After large expansion days, be cautious as price may shift into a new phase.",
